<h2>About Page Rank</h2>
<p>PageRank, named after Larry Page, is one of several metrics Google uses to determine search result rankings. </p>
<p>It is an indication of how important Google believes a page is, based on how many other web pages link to it and how "important" those web pages are. (What PageRank the linking pages have.)</p>
<p>Other metrics that search engines use in determining results include the load time of the website, the validity of the markup, and above all, the content of the website.</p>